vides wireless networking to mediumsized and larger businesses in  aerohive was listed on the wall street journals list of top  startups the company raised around  million in venture capital funding before undergoing an ipo in march  historyedit aerohive was founded in  by changming liu that same year the company raised  million in series a round funding in july  the company raised an additional  million in series b round funding led by kleiner perkins caufield  byers aerohive completed a series c round of funding raising  million to expand its sales and marketing strategy in march  in  the company acquired pareto networks a cloudbased routing service the acquisition allowed aerohive to integrate parets cloud management technology into its existing offerings in september  aerohive raised  million in a series e round of funding and announced its plans to undergo an ipo the following year the company raised an additional  million in funding as it prepared to go public in  on march   the company was listed on the new york stock exchange under the hive symbol aerohive joined barack obamas connected initiative in october  when it partnered with apple inc and provided wireless connectivity to the schools receiving apple products aerohive announced that its devices would operate more seamlessly with barracuda networks security products in may  in september  the company announced a technology alliance with juniper networks in january  the company released hiveschool a learning application for k classrooms that runs on any network with any computer running the google chrome web browser the company announced that it had entered a distribution agreement with synnex corporation in february  the agreement named synnex as the exclusive distributor of aerohive products in canada in april  aerohive announced a strategic partnership with the technology company dell in september  the company released sdlan a softwaredefined network that functions on local area networks operationsedit aerohive develops a controllerless lan architecture called cooperative control which provides all the performance availability management mobility and security needed in a large campus deployment this architecture also enables secure scalable highperformance and missioncritical wireless networking in a manageable and costeffective way to industries such as education distributed enterprises retail healthcare state and local government and manufacturing the company also develops an operating system hiveos for access points and switches a cloud enabled management system hivemanager wifi planning tools applications and network administration tools for its devices the company makes available open rest apis to its cloud platform aerohive cloud services for developers to build wifi management and analytics solutions in september  aerohive announced an update to its cloud management system hivemanager ng which enabled lan networks to become softwaredefined referencesedit  aerohive networks inc   aerohive networks inc profile   a b ludwig sean september   cloudbased networking startup aerohive networks readies for ipo with m funding grab venturebeat retrieved  november    rao leena march   cloudbased networking company aerohive networks raises  million techcrunch retrieved  november    looking for the next big thing ranking the top  startups   deals of the day jos a bank buying eddie bauer   a b aerohive networks files for  million ipo   aerohive adds  million the pe hub network  july    aerohive networks secures  series c financing round xconomy  march    berndtson chad  august  aerohive gains partners and finally a buzz in wlan channel crn   berndston chad november   cisco competitors say meraki move makes them more attractive crn magazine retrieved  november    the daily startup aerohive buzzes with m led by ivp amid sweet mobile connectivity demand wall street journal september   retrieved  november    wexler joanie  january  aerohive buys cloud startup pareto networks 